library(tidyverse)
library(magrittr)
library(car)
library(alr3)
library(corrplot)

Data

This data set comes from the UCI Machine Learning Repository and can be found here. According to the data abstract, this data set consists of posts published during the year of 2014 on the Facebook pages of a renowned cosmetics brand. The data set contains 500 rows and 19 variables about each post.

facebook <- read.csv(file = '../data/Facebook_metrics/dataset_Facebook.csv', sep = ';')
plot(facebook)

X <- facebook$consumers
hist(X, breaks = 200)

shapiro.test(bcPower(X, powerTransform(X)$lambda))
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  bcPower(X, powerTransform(X)$lambda)
## W = 0.98669, p-value = 0.0001567
facebook$X_trans <- bcPower(X, powerTransform(X)$lambda)
hist(facebook$X_trans, breaks = 30)

Y <- facebook$engaged_users
hist(Y, breaks = 200)

shapiro.test(bcPower(Y, powerTransform(Y)$lambda))
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  bcPower(Y, powerTransform(Y)$lambda)
## W = 0.98103, p-value = 4.192e-06
facebook$Y_trans <- bcPower(Y, powerTransform(Y)$lambda)
hist(facebook$Y_trans, breaks = 30)

plot(X, Y)
abline(lsfit(X, Y))

summary(lm(Y ~ X))

shapiro.test(lm(Y_trans ~ X_trans, data = facebook)$residuals)

##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test

par(mfrow = c(2,2))
plot(lm(Y ~ X))

par(mfrow = c(2,2))
plot(lm(Y_trans ~ X_trans, data = facebook))

model <- lm(Y_trans ~ X_trans, data = facebook)
anova(model, update(model, ~.-X_trans))
